The Heritrix start/stop/shutdown was recently refactored to accomodate 
multiple instances of Heritrix in same &#39;container&#39; as well as 
registration/deregistration of Heritrix instances and jobs with JMX and 
JNDI.   This work may have inadvertently broken the way you embed Heritrix.

Have you tried enabling CrawlController to log at level FINE or FINER? 
Might give clue on why we&#39;re shortcircuting job shutdown?  But I 
guessing your usage is bypassing some newly-added deregistrations now 
necessary letting go of a job. If you paste in the code, I can take a look.

You might try using the same methods the UI and JMX uses? (See 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/Heritrix.html#281 
for listing of published JMX operations or checkout the 1.5 JVM&#39;s 
jconsole application to see a &#39;prettier&#39; listing).  Going via these 
methods will be safer in the long run.  These published methods are less 
likely to change over time.

Sorry for any inconvenience caused.
Yours,
St.Ack



